      does it seem reasonable, as craig mentions, to have both
      *.inter.net hosts and *.sri.com hosts on the same class B network?

Absolutely.  If there's anyone on this list who hasn't grasped the
100% total independence between host names and network addresses
yet, then perhaps you should grab a copy of the archives, and reread
from the beginning.

